Signals with size 1 are regarded by Busmaster as Boolean and than as signed independent of what is selected .This is wrong, because signed signals with length 1 are shown in 3d party tools as "-1" instead of "1" .
So booleans should be unsigned or selcted in the GUI configuration should not be overwritten!
The problem is loclized in code as follows:

----------------
    // errors eliminated now do necessary conversions

    **if(m_ucLength == 1)** // single bit - change type to bool

    {

        **m_ucType = SIG_TYPE_BOOL;**

    }

 

**for Boolean they always write “-“**
 

        if ((m_ucType == SIG_TYPE_UINT) || (m_ucType == SIG_TYPE_UINT64)) //<------------------------false for BOOL

        {

            fileOutput << "+";

        }

        else

        {

            fileOutput << "-";   //<------------------------------------------------------------------This place

        }

