Busmaster 3.1.0 (with patch for channel configuration issue #1036 )

When i try to send a signal waveform using an extended data frame identifier (29bit), a wrong frame is sent on can bus with a standard identifier (11bit).
Statistic windows show that only standard frame is sent (and the product i currently develop receive 11bit frame too).

I suppose a small bug was located in WaveformTransmitter.cpp  ,source code seem don't care about frame identifier type defined in database  (only id, length and channel are set, no identifier type)
@Line : 267
 ```
      // Get message and signal details from database.
