I think that if you used Trace() to see i you would find that i is
incrementing and that there is probably something wrong with your can
message.  Instead of using a database, trying using a raw STCAN_MSG and
populate the first byte, like the code below.  Also make sure that i is
defined as a compatible type.  I add `#include <inttypes.h>` to all of
my simulations and use uint8_t for single byte values.

Also note that as of 2.6.4 all handlers are started automatically on
connect.

