When using a converted CAPL script which intercepts messages to calculate CRC and live counter the node simulation sends both the manipulated message and the ones with calculated CRC/counter. CANalyzer only sends the manipulated messages. Is there a way to natively do this in the converted C++ file?
CAPL Code snippet:

```
on message CAN1.EVCM_PE_01
{
  if ((this.EVCM_PE_01_counter == 0) && (this.EVCM_PE_01_checksum == 0))
  {
    message CAN1.EVCM_PE_01 msg_EVCM_PE_01;

    msg_EVCM_PE_01 = this; 
    msg_EVCM_PE_01.EVCM_PE_01_counter = ++mc_EVCM_PE_01 & 0x0f;
    msg_EVCM_PE_01.EVCM_PE_01_checksum = CRC( msg_EVCM_PE_01);

    output( msg_EVCM_PE_01);
    //writeEx( 1, 1, "%d ", msg_EVCM_PE_01.EVCM_PE_01_counter);
  }
}
```

