I want to use a node simulation to define and send database messages. I wrote suitable code for my task. The code looks like follows:

void OnTimer_txMsg10ms_10( )
{

//definition of can messages
DataBaseMessage msgDataBase = { 0x200, 1, 0, 7, 1, { 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0 },1 };

//signal values
msgDataBase.m_sWhichBit.signal1=1;
msgDataBase.m_sWhichBit.signal2=2;
msgDataBase.m_sWhichBit.signal3=3;
msgDataBase.m_sWhichBit.signal4=4;
msgDataBase.m_sWhichBit.signal5=5;
msgDataBase.m_sWhichBit.signal6=6;

//send message
SendMsg(_((STCAN_MSG_)&msgDataBase));

}

After starting the node simulation I can see all the messages I have defined in the node simulation in the message window as RX-messages. That means the node simulation works fine. The only problem is that I want to send the messages to a control unit but it doesn't work to send the messages. The control unit cannot receive the messages. I also have tested the "Transmit" function of busmaster. The result was that everything works fine. So I can exclude that there is some problem with my hardware.

Actually I want to know if it is possible to create tx-messages with the node simulation and if it is possible it would be greate get some hints what I have done wrong.

Thanks a lot!

