Hello Tobias,

Looks like the database is not properly defined. From the above declared union comments, it indicates that Byte 3 is unused, but there is no space allocated for that. If Byte 3 is unused, the definition should be similar to this:

typedef union 
{
    unsigned char      m_aucData[8];
    unsigned short int m_auwData[4];
    unsigned long  int m_aulData[2];

```
struct
{
    int          Checksum_2F2     :  8 ;    // using Byte 0, OK
    int          MessageCounter_2F2 :  4 ;  // using Byte 1, first 4 bits, OK
    int          MinTorqueLimit   : 11 ;    // using Byte 1 ( remaining 4Bits) and byte 2 (7 Bits), OK

    unsigned int                  :  9 ;    // Unused bits byte 2(1 Bit) and byte 3(8 Bits ), OK

    int          MaxTorqueGradient : 15 ;   // using Byte 4 and 5!!! Byte 3 is not used
    int          MaxTorqueLimit   : 11 ;
    unsigned int                  :  6 ;

};
```

}VCU_INV_03_;

